docs.abstract: I’ve celebrated this holiday all my life. It’s different this year.
docs.snippet: I’ve celebrated this holiday all my life. It’s different this year.
docs.lead_paragraph: For me, celebrating Juneteenth was like planning a birthday party or hosting a family reunion. My father organized the first Juneteenth gathering in Grand Prairie, Texas, in 1987 and continued his efforts throughout my childhood, implanting me in the process. Weeks before the holiday, my family and our friends would draft itineraries and search for soul food caterers, trying to create an environment different from the previous year’s, to keep people excited about attending, on a tight budget.

headline.main: Juneteenth Is a Reminder That Freedom Wasn’t Just Handed Over
